      "url": "https://risingsunoverport.co.za/53147/kzn-hosts-fast-bowler-search/",
      "host": "risingsunoverport.co.za",
      "text": "Local sport KZN hosts fast bowler search It is currently taking place around the country and identifies a number of talented local young bowlers who will be given the chance to prove themselves in front of CSA’s development structures. 7 mins ago Mfuneko Ngam briefing all of the fast bowlers. \nThe search for South Africa’s next great fast bowler continued, last week. The initiative, which is led by Audi, Cricket South Africa (CSA) and former Proteas quick and development guru, Mfuneko Ngam, is the first designed to utilise state-of-the-art technology to unearth the hidden gems of South African fast blowing. \nIt is currently taking place around the country and identifies a number of talented local young bowlers who will be given the chance to prove themselves in front of CSA’s development structures. \nLead talent scout, Mfuneko Ngam, said, “Our first events in Gauteng and Eastern Cape were resounding successes and this was no different. I have been very impressed by the level of talent we have uncovered so far. We are very excited at the prospect of one of these young bowlers following in the footsteps of the great Proteas bowlers who came before them.” \nOn the day, local bowlers between the ages of 15 and 18 were given the opportunity to showcase their talent in front of a powerful development team. \nBowlers were given the chance to illustrate their skills in the nets with the most promising selected to have their bowling measured on the Audi Bowling Lab – a set-up which utilises state-of-the-art PitchVision technology to instantly analyse a bowler’s performance by comparing pace, line, length, deviation and bounce to that of a current Proteas bowler. \nNgam and his team, which included CSA representatives and local coaches, utilised the scoring system of the Audi Bowling Lab to select the talented boys and girls who will now be put in front of CSA development structures. \nTrevor Hill, head of Audi South Africa, said, “Today continued our search for standout fast bowlers and Durban did not disappoint. As progressive partner to the Proteas, Audi is proud to be able to take our partnership with CSA to the next level by driving progress in a development space. The prospect of potentially uncovering the next Ntini or Ngam, together with CSA, is something we are not only excited by but which we are striving towards.” SHARE",
