      "text": "BBOG condoles with US over soldiers’ death By Latifat Opoola | Publish Date: Oct 24 2017 2:30AM (0 Likes) \nThe #BringBackOurGirls movement has extended condolences to the government and people of the United States of America over its soldiers killed in an ambush in Niger Republic. \nThe movement expressed the condolence in a statement issued by the group’s conveners, Oby Ezekwesili and Florence Ozor, in Abuja yesterday. \nQuoting the US Navy Lieutenant Commander Anthony Falvo, the group said the US forces were in Niger to provide training and security assistance to the Nigerien Armed Forces, including support for intelligence, surveillance and reconnaissance efforts, in their efforts to target violent extremist organizations in the region. \nIt also said part of the training was to assist and advice the Nigeriens in order to increase their ability to bring stability and security to their people. (0 Likes) What do you think about this story Please include a contact number if you are willing to speak to a Daily Trust journalist. You can also contact us in the following way: Name",
