      "title": "Lagos Lawmaker Donates Computer Set To APC Secretariat",
      "country": "NG",
      "crawl_date": "2017-10-24T11:32:28Z",
      "url": "http://independent.ng/lagos-lawmaker-donates-computer-set-to-apc-secretariat/",
      "host": "independent.ng",
      "text": "Posted in Daily Independent Lagos Lawmaker Donates Computer Set To APC Secretariat \nHonourable Jude Emeka Idimogu, a member representing Oshodi-Isolo Constituency 02, has reaffirmed his commitment to serve his constituents, saying he remained an All Progressive Congress (APC) loyalist. \nIdimogu stated this why presenting a computer set to Isolo Local Government APC secretariat during the party monthly Local Government Area (LGA) meeting at Ishaga-tedo, Isolo Local Council Development Area (LCDA), Lagos. \nPresenting the computer set to Chief Lawal Raji, the LGA party Chairman, Idimogu pledged his commitment to serve his constituents better than ever. \nIdimogu who was a PDP lawmaker in the state Assembly defected to the ruling APC early this year. \nHe said, “I remain an APC loyalist and I will continue to serve you to the best of my ability because I always love to make my impact whenever I find myself.” \n“I defected to this party due to the conviction and friendship I received from the state Governor, Mr. Akinwunmi Ambode, and all members of the Lagos State House of Assembly. \n“I’m not treated as an Igbo man but treated like one of them, the Governor treat all LASHA members equally, so I have no choice than to join the moving train, the only party that ruled Lagos since inception of Democracy in this country is APC,” he said. \nSpeaking on the achievements of the state governor, he said the progress of the state was not negotiable and called the Ndigbo residents in the state to support the state governor and APC in order to move the state forward. \n“I call all Ndigbo in Lagos to join APC and as well support our dear Governor for the progress of the state, Lagos belong to all of us, there is no discrimination in Lagos; Lagosians are very accommodating, they have taken us as their family, let us work together for a better Lagos; it is where you live and trade that you protect, let’s protect our dear state and forget the issue of tribalism, he posited. \nIn his address, Hon. Shamsideen Olaleye, the Isolo LCDA Chairman, appreciated all party faithful for their support during the last Local Government election, saying he would fulfill all his campaign promises. \n“We promised that we are going to touch your lives and this we will fulfill it by God’s grace,” he stated. \nSpeaking on his achievements within two and a half months in office, he said he has worked on some roads within the LCDA, saying the rain has not allowed it government to construct some of his proposed roads. \n“In his speech, Chief Lawal Raji, the LGA party Chairman, appreciated Hon. Idimogu for his gesture and called on the party members to always see Idimogu as one of them. \nHe said the LGA was so lucky to have a man like Idimogu as it representative at the state level.",
