      "text": "Eric Phiri | October 23, 2017 \nAfter a string of successful book signing events in Johannesburg and Paris, Bonang ‘Queen B’ Matheba is set to host a book signing of her book ‘Bonang: From A to B’ in Lagos, Nigeria on Sunday, 29 October at Cocoon, Ikoyi. \nThe book which chronicles her journey from being a girl from Mafikeng in the North West, South Africa; to becoming the globally successful, multi-talented businesswoman and TV/radio personality that she is today was released early July and has claimed the number one spot as a best seller at Exclusive Books, SA. \nThe Paris book signing was a huge success boasting attendance by South Africa’s most prominent lifestyle television show, Top Billing, who will be flighting the signing in November. \nMatheba has also been invited to attend the Lagos Fashion and Design Week, a leading fashion event on the global fashion calendar showcasing the latest and hottest collections by African designers. She will feature in a session hosted by BellaNaija.com on Saturday 28th October at the LFDW grounds at Eko Atlantic. \nThe book signing will be spent showering her fans and friends with love and signing copies of her revamped book. \nThe new edition of the book is nothing short of amazing, with new additions of facts, informative chapters and advice that will change the way people look at life, especially those that look up to her. \nA series of book signing in various countries and cities will follow and these include London, Namibia, Botswana and National cities.",
