      "text": "Winnie Rust murder: Husband never trusted accused Nigel Plaaitjies on Monday pleaded guilty to robbing Rust in May last year, but denied killing her. FILE: Winnie Rust. Picture: Facebook Shamiela Fisher | one hour ago \nCAPE TOWN - Murdered author Winnie Rust ’s husband has testified that he never trusted the youth who is implicated in her murder in Wellington. \nNigel Plaaitjies on Monday pleaded guilty to robbing Rust in May last yea r, but denied killing her. \nThe 20-year-old's uncle Johannes Plaaitjies has pleaded not guilty to all charges against him. \nHermanus Rust says he and the deceased were married for 53 years. \nThe retired doctor says that he was shocked when he stumbled across his wife's body on the kitchen floor after having taken an afternoon nap. \nThe 87-year-old has testified that her hands and feet were bound, tape was placed over her mouth and a scarf covered her face. \nThe Rust family met Nigel Plaaitjies while he was attending primary school. \nHis mother was a domestic worker for their daughter. \nRust says his wife was very fond of the 20-year-old and paid for his schooling and athletic activities. \nHe says that she was busy helping him get his driver's licence at the time of her murder. \nRust says he didn't trust Plaaitjies and felt that he manipulated his wife. \n(Edited by Shimoney Regter)",
