      "text": "News A date has been set With an amazing R68 408.90 raised thus far, and deposited into crowd-funding account Backabuddy, hairdresser Mandy Lottering has now been booked into hospital on November 6 scheduled to have her double mastectomy. about 1 hour ago Mandy Lottering will have her double mastectomy on the 6th of November \n\n\n\nMandy’s desperate plight to raise the funds for her mastectomy after she was diagnosed with stage 3 cancer – invasive ductal carcinoma – was highlighted in the Maritzburg Sun and online at www.maritzburgsun.co.za and funds began to pour in. \nIn desperate need to have the mastectomy done at a private hospital as the waiting list at government hospitals is 8 months, Mandy took to social media to explain her crisis of needing a minimum of R120 000 to ensure the operation that rendered her a chance at life again. The follow-up chemotherapy and radiation will be done at Grey’s Hospital. \nThe first R40 000 raised was to pay for her Anaesthetist and Surgeon, the second R40 000 (which is almost there) is the deposit for the hospital, while the remaining R40 000 still to be raised, will be the outstanding amount for the hospital stay. \nMandy’s cause has brought many Pietermaritzburg’s residents together to assist this woman, who herself, is someone who has constantly given back to those less fortunate. A huge fundraiser will be held in the first weekend of December, with an auction and stunning raffle prizes to be won. Read more about Mandy’s journey and contribute to her cause here: https://www.backabuddy.co.za/mandys-tatas SHARE",
