      "host": "punchng.com",
      "text": "Posted in Punch Newspaper Police arrest 12 robbery suspects in Ondo \nThe Ondo State Police Command has arrested 12 persons in connection with robberies in the state. \nThe suspects include Friday Odiri, Monday Odiri, Monday Abiodun, Akintunde Henry, Abiodun Tunde, Ayodele Ayobami and Ayoh Genesis. \nOthers are Oluwafemi Ayodeji, Kola Ogunbiyi, Seun Ayodele, Ogonejobo Partick and Felix Ugwuanyi. \nParading the suspects on Monday at the police command headquarters in Akure, the state capital, the Police Public Relations Officer, Mr. Femi Joseph, said the men were arrested at different locations in the state, adding that they had been allegedly terrorising the residents. \nJoseph explained that some of the suspects robbed their victims on highways, while others snatched vehicles and motorcycles at gunpoint. \nHe said items recovered from the suspects included guns and cutlasses, adding that they had confessed to various crimes, as well as being members of cults. \nThe police spokesman stated that some suspected robbers fled dring police raids, noting that efforts were ongoing to arrest them. \n“Investigation is in progress and these suspects would be charged to court as soon as possible,” he added. \nCopyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. (Visited 1 times, 1",
