      "text": "#CrimeStats: The 10 statistics you need to know Justice & Safety / 24 October 2017, 10:30am / Staff Reporter Police Minister Fikile Mbalula presented the 2016/17 crime statistics report in Parliament on Tuesday. Below are ten of the most important statistics from his report: * In 2016/2017 financial year, approximately 2.1 million serious crime counts were recorded, of which 1 738 980 were community-reported serious crimes. #sapsHQ Contact related Crime #CrimeStats : Trend over ten year period. ME pic.twitter.com/mox8KMkTPj — SA Police Service (@SAPoliceService) October 24, 2017 * Serious crime decreased by 1.8 percent on the previous year. * The murder rate is down by 1.8 percent #sapsHQ Contact Crime #CrimeStats : #TrioCrimes : Highlights. Provincial Breakdown (total & percentage change). ME pic.twitter.com/ygmZmRlb3v — SA Police Service (@SAPoliceService) October 24, 2017 * Carjacking has increased by 14.5 percent * Sexual offences decreased by 4.3 percent * Assault GBH down by 6.7 percent * Aggravated robbery increased by 6.4 percent — SA Police Service (@SAPoliceService) October 24, 2017 * Robbery decreased by 1.3 percent * Common assault decreased by 5.2 percent #sapsHQ Contact Crime #CrimeStats : Sexual Offence: Sexual Assault: Provincial Overview-actual. ME pic.twitter.com/p31UrSdqPF — SA Police Service (@SAPoliceService) October 24, 2017 * Attempted murder down by 0.4 percent IOL",
