      "url": "http://www.dailysun.co.za/News/National/too-many-killings-in-mzansi-20171024",
      "host": "dailysun.co.za",
      "text": "#CrimeStats: TOO MANY KILLINGS IN MZANSI! By Sun Reporter Tuesday, October 24, 2017 10:25 ~ \nTHERE'S just too many people being killed in Mzansi. \nThe 2016/17 crime statistics revealed that the murder rate in Mzansi has gone up by 1.8%. \nPresenting the statistics to Parliament's Portfolio Committee on Police, Major General Sekhukhune reported a total of 19016 murders for the 2016/2017 financial year. \nHe said murder has increased in 4 of the 9 provinces. \nIn Gauteng murder is up 6,7%, Mpumalanga is 11,1%, Western Cape 2,7%, Kwazulu-Natal 2.2%. \nAttempted murder has also gone up by 3.2%. \nRobbery with aggravating has increased in all 9 provinces. \nThe is also a 0.9% increase in the number of sexual assaults reported to police in 2016/2017 financial year. \nMinister @Police minister Fikile Mbalula said alcohol and substance abuse have been found to have played a major role in contact crimes. \nOther stats are as follows: Assault GBH decreased by 6.7% Common assault decreased by 5.2% Sexual offences has decreased by 4.3% Murder's gone up by 4.6% Aggravated robbery up by 6.4% Property-related crime experienced a decrease of 0.5%. Comment on this story",
