      "text": "Telecom Operations Management Market: Overview \n\nTelecom operations management caters to abridge the intricate day-to-day operations taking place in the telecommunication sector. In a bid to obtain the maximum market share in terms of subscribers, telecom operators have lessen their calling costs which results in less productivity and lower average revenue per user (ARPU) values. As a consequence, they face a rising task of reducing their operational expenditure and maximizing productivity. Ever-increasing requirement for end-to-end inclusive solution for the running of operations led to the development of this market. \n\nhttps://www.zionmarketresearch.com/report/telecom-operations-management-market \n\nThe global telecom operations management market has been experiencing higher development over the coming years owing to augmented requirement for telecom companies to successfully and timely address different customer needs in highly competitive atmosphere. Telecom companies acquire high expenditure while refinement of their operations and look for operations support system (OSS) providers to offer efficient telecom services with condensed OPEX and CAPEX cost. \n\nTelecom Operations Management Market: Growth Factors \n\nIncreasing operational costs, rising acceptance of next-generation telecom technologies, high operational complexity, and high investments in OSS structural design are the most important aspects contributing to the market development. \n\nHigh operational expenditure and difficulty of telecom infrastructure, as a result it has augmented the popularity for the global telecom operations management market. Shortage of competent system integrators is anticipated to hold back market expansion over the coming years. Rising requirement for end-to-end operations administration is anticipated to open up latest avenues for market development.",
