      "text": "Home Business & Economy NSE partially lifts suspension on Oando shares NSE partially lifts suspension on Oando shares Business & Economy Oct 24, 2017 \nThe Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) says it has partially lifted the suspension placed on shares belonging to Oando Plc. General Counsel, head of regulation, NSE, Tinuade Awe in a notice said starting from Monday, October 23, Oando shares will be available to trading though trading activity will not lead to a change in price. \n“Dealing members are referred to our market bulletins of Wednesday, October 18, 2017 (NSE/LARD/LRD/MB05/17/10/18) notifying them that effective Friday, October 20, 2017 and until further directive, the shares of Oando Plc (“Oando” or “the company”) will be placed on technical suspension; and that of Friday, October 20, 2017 (NSE/LARD/LRD/MB07/17/10/20) informing them that the shares of Oando were still on full suspension as the process of converting from full to technical suspension was yet to be completed. \n“Please be informed that effective today, Monday, October 23, 2017; the shares of Oando Plc have been placed on technical suspension. Thus, the shares will be available for trading but there will be no price movement while the technical suspension subsists,” the statement read. \nOando Plc shares was suspended after Securities Exchange Commission (SEC) accused it of; breach of the provisions of the Investments & Securities Act 2007, breach of the SEC Code of Corporate Governance for Public Companies, suspected insider dealing, related party transactions not conducted at arm’s length, and discrepancies in the shareholding structure of Oando Plc. On Thursday, the Johannesburg Stock Exchange also placed a ban on Oando on request of SEC.",
